The Presidency has confirmed receiving Part 4 of the State Capture report. The Part 4 of the report deals with eight topics, including state capture at Eskom, the closure of the Gupta brothers’ bank accounts and the Free State housing and asbestos scandals. The Chairperson of the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture Chief Justice Raymond Zondo is expected to deliver the fifth and final instalment of the report by mid-June. This after the North Gauteng High Court in Pretoria extended the commission’s deadline by six weeks. Earlier in March, President Ramaphosa received Part 3 of the State Capture Report. The four-part report zoomed in on Bosasa, now African Global Operations. It alleged that the company was used as a front to get kickbacks in exchange for lucrative government contracts. The video below looks at the State Capture Report Part 3: 